# .worktreeinclude - files copied into new `claude --worktree` checkouts.
# https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees
#
# Uses .gitignore syntax. Only files that BOTH match a pattern here AND are
# git-ignored are copied, so tracked files (e.g. .dev.vars.example) are never
# duplicated. This lets a fresh worktree run `make dev` without hand-copying
# local Cloudflare Workers secrets.

# Cloudflare Workers local secrets
**/.dev.vars
**/.dev.vars.*

# Global environment files
**/.env
**/.env.*
